						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Oziphantom wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">you have ~1 million bits per second, so it depends on how you want to use them.</div><br />Actually, that one website TOUKO just linked said it could transfer 4MB in one second, so 32x as much data, which is a world of difference...<br /><br />4 * 8 * 1024 * 1024 / 60 = 559,240 bits per frame,<br />6 * 320 * 200 = 384,000 bits per screen,<br />559,240 / 384,000 = about 1.46 screens per frame.<br /><br />Of course, this isn't including any sort of overhead for setting everything up. Does the Amiga have some sort of display list for Copper, or what?</div>

